doc/source/admin/upgrades/distribution-u.message:
If you don't clear a node from the cluster, you'll get something like this;

fatal: [grown-cobra_rabbit_mq_container-76a90bd4]: FAILED! => {"attempts": 5, "changed": true, "cmd": ["rabbitmqctl", "join_cluster", "rabbit@guided-fawn-rabbit-mq-container-dd97ecb8"], "msg": "non-zero return code", "rc": 70, "stderr": "Error:\n{:inconsistent_cluster, 'Node \\'rabbit@guided-fawn-rabbit-mq-container-dd97ecb8\\' thinks it\\'s clustered with node \\'rabbit@grown-cobra-rabbit-mq-container-76a90bd4\\', but \\'rabbit@grown-cobra-rabbit-mq-container-76a90bd4\\' disagrees'}", "stdout": "Clustering node rabbit@grown-cobra-rabbit-mq-container-76a90bd4 with rabbit@guided-fawn-rabbit-mq-container-dd97ecb8"}

You're introducing a new node with the same name (that has no state). So the cluster needs to forget about the old one to accept a new one.

